        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-23 09:52:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nnot sure if I understand the whole mechanism. my idea was originally to just remove all the path logic and extra args, and ansible would just mount tmpfs on /var/lib/etcd, so that rke will do the rest without any change. and you said that doesn't work, or I misunderstood?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "f3f28894bae97516f4b76aac12c13aeab057c7ca",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4886,
          "name": "Petr Ospalý",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "p.ospaly@email.cz",
          "username": "p.ospaly"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-23 10:01:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis commit is able to do two things: set custom path to etcd storage - which does not have to be hardwired to /var/lib/etcd and second feature is to prepare tmpfs for such storage - usage of which should be only for  testing/development stuff and never used in production.\n\nCurrently these two stuff I made intertwined, my propose to keep them separate: \n\n1. custom path to storage but no tmpfs\n2. leave default path but use tmpfs\n3. both",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
